<div class="question-block">
<div class="question-header">
  <span class="question-pts">10 pts</span>
  <span class="question-title">Q6 — Approximate Q-Learning</span>
  <span class="question-dep">Depends on Q3 + Q4</span>
</div>
<div class="question-body">
<p>Instead of storing Q-values per state, learn <strong>feature weights</strong> that generalize:</p>
<pre><code>Q(s,a) = Σ_i  w_i · f_i(s,a)

difference = [r + γ · max_{a'} Q(s',a')] − Q(s,a)
w_i ← w_i + α · difference · f_i(s,a)</code></pre>
<p>Implement <code>get_q_value</code> (dot product) and <code>update</code> (weight update) in <code>ApproximateQAgent</code>.</p>
<p>Features from <code>TerrainExtractor</code> include:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>closest-sample-distance</code> — normalized Manhattan distance to nearest sample</li>
  <li><code>#-of-craters-1-step-away</code> — count of adjacent crater cells</li>
  <li><code>moves-toward-sample</code> — 1.0 if action reduces distance to goal</li>
  <li><code>bias</code> — constant 1.0</li>
</ul>
<pre><code># Identity features (should match tabular Q-learning):
python mars_rover.py -a q -g small_grid -k 100

# Terrain features — generalizes to large grids:
python mars_rover.py -a q -g large_grid -k 60
python mars_rover.py -a q -g huge_grid -k 100

python autograder.py -q q6</code></pre>
</div>
